<br>
If we have enough room, and several people need epic pieces (besides the ones reserved for PC) we could do a random for those that need them so everyone would have a chance....this just all sort of depends on who is going etc.  I haven't seen anyone say they need the SSOC's, but PC would also like to reserve 3 of those.  (6 drop - so 3 more available for needing rangers)<br>
<br>
Crowns - we are reserving one, so that leaves a chance for 2 more.<br>
<br>
Blades - we are reserving 2.  The thing with this guy is he can be incredibly giving and spawn with a blade each time or he can be incredibly stingy and take several kills to get one.  So here is my plan for this - we will get the 2 blades we need and then kill until one spawns with a guest blade.  IF the next bird spawns with a sword we will kill it if there is another warrior there that needs it....but if he spawns empty handed after we get the 3rd blade we will move on. (the next islands take a bit of skill and time to get through so we don't want to spend too terribly long in one place)<br>
<br>
I am also asking that if you come for this raid you come for the WHOLE THING!! So be prepared to be raiding for about 6 hours that day.  You also MUST follow my instructions, group leaders etc at all times...if for any reason you are disruptive or  cause the raid problems, you will be asked to leave.  this raid takes a lot of patience!  There are many things that death touch, there are spawns to be aware of etc, so please be patient and understand we will be working to accomplish our goals....it just takes some time.<br>
<br>
As long as everyone cooperates we can get this done in a fair amount of time.  Late comers are not allowed unless ok'd by me ahead of time.  (because there is no COTH...when someone joins late it's a matter of porting them in, having them die, porting them in again and summoning their corpse....can you say pain in the butt?! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> )  <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://hometown.aol.com/pmoriarty143/myhomepage/anezkiatynsil.gif" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><br>
